articles.author: Barbara Sprunt
articles.title: With the outlook for SNAP benefits uncertain, food banks are warning of a crisis - NPR
articles.description: More Americans are turning to food banks to help fill the assistance gap, but administrators caution they aren't designed to act as a safety net for a government program.
articles.content:
More than 40 million Americans who rely on federal food assistance woke up to uncertainty on Saturday over whether their aid is secure or when it will resume in full.
